<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Air Quality Results for <%= city %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Air Quality Results for <%= city %></h1>
        <p>Check the current air quality levels for different pollutants.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <% if (data) { %>
            <div class="aqi-display">
                <h2>Overall AQI: <%= data.overall_aqi %></h2> 
                <p>The overall Air Quality Index (AQI) is a summary of the pollution levels for the following pollutants:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>CO: <%= data.CO.aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data.CO.concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                    <li>NO2: <%= data.NO2.aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data.NO2.concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                    <li>O3: <%= data.O3.aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data.O3.concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                    <li>SO2: <%= data.SO2.aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data.SO2.concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                    <li>PM2.5: <%= data['PM2.5'].aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data['PM2.5'].concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                    <li>PM10: <%= data.PM10.aqi %> (Concentration: <%= data.PM10.concentration %> µg/m³)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        <% } else { %>
            <p>Data is not available for the selected city or there was an error fetching the data.</p>
        <% } %>
        <a href="/">Check another city</a>
    </div>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 Air Quality Index Checker. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
    <script src="/script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
